news.title: NCLT admits Piramal Capital's insolvency plea in Rs 1,065-crore default by developer
news.para: The Mumbai bench of the National Company Law Tribunal has also appointed Jayesh Natvarlal Sanghrajka as the resolution professional for the company.

news.title: Noida: No water in Panchsheel Hynish for a week, residents go to kin
news.para: Residents said they visited their friends and relatives as there was no water in their washrooms and kitchens. On Thursday, they discussed the matter with the district magistrate.

news.title: Bollywood writer, director Krishna DK buys duplex for Rs 35.50 crore in Mumbai
news.para: As part of the deal, the buyers will also get ownership rights to a 1.62% land parcel of the Tower Windsor Grande Residences, which also counts other Bollywood personalities, including actors and leading singers, as apartment owners.

news.title: Investment opportunities V exits PNB Housing; sells entire stake for Rs 2,106 crore
news.para: ​According to the block deal data available with the BSE, Investment Opportunities V Pte Ltd offloaded more than 2.56 crore shares, amounting to a 9.88 per cent stake in PNB Housing Finance.

news.title: China regulator urges banks to grant financing for property projects
news.para: Financial institutions should not blindly withdraw and cut off loans for eligible property projects that have encountered temporary difficulties on construction, Xiao Yuanqi, deputy director of the NFRA, said at a news conference.

news.title: London-focused Workspace Group's CEO to step down this year
news.para: Clemett, 63, leaves at a time when flexible space operators such as Workspace have outperformed the traditional landlords on the operational front in the UK, as tenants opt for short-term leases and reassess their strategies periodically amid lingering broader economic worries.

news.title: SC refuses bail to Radius Group's MD in Yes Bank money laundering case
news.para: A bench of Justices Bela M Trivedi and Pankaj Mithal said the offence is serious and the high court considered everything. The counsel appearing for Chhabria then withdrew the plea and the matter was dismissed as withdrawn.

news.title: ACC's profit soars four-fold to Rs 537.67 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: ACC's revenue from operations was up 8.31 per cent to Rs 4,914.36 crore during the quarter under review. It was Rs 4,536.97 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: Mumbai police's EOW searches premises of Supreme Constructions' director in cheating case
news.para: The Mumbai police had last week registered a first information report (FIR) against Tekchandani, his wife, the directors of his company Supreme Constructions and a few others at the Chembur police station.

news.title: China Evergrande offshore bondholder group to join liquidation petition: Sources
news.para: The bondholder group owns more than $2 billion in offshore notes guaranteed by Evergrande and its support to a winding-up petition against the world's most indebted developer could increase the chances of an immediate liquidation order from the court, lawyers in the industry said.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body issues notices to 2,500 commercial units over fire safety norms
news.para: It may be noted that the Pimpri Chinchwad Municipal Corporation (PCMC) initiated around 250 women from self-help groups to conduct a fire safety survey of all commercial establishments in October last year.

news.title: Over 14 lakh land records in tahsildar's office still await digitization in Dharwad
news.para: In a bid to protect age-old records pertaining to land and other properties, to ensure transparency in administration, the Karnataka revenue minister is also insisting that all revenue offices be converted into e-offices.

news.title: Raheja Developers' 'Special 26 Extravaganza' unveils unbelievable Republic Day deals for the Delhi Mall investors
news.para: For investors who want to invest in real estate, look no further than Raheja Developers' 'Special 26 Extravaganza' for the Delhi Mall. This exclusive opportunity not only assures substantial savings but also sets investors up for sustained long-term financial growth.

news.title: Indore: IDA approves Rs 320 crore for development projects
news.para: An approval was given for Rs 320 crore for developing Rs 81.30 crore flyover at Mhow Naka square, Rs 44 crore flyover at Marimata square and Rs 38.5 crore flyover at Bada Ganpati square.

news.title: Kanpur development body allots house through lottery to 1,152 beneficiaries
news.para: KDA has constructed around 1152 houses under Prime Minister Awas Scheme at Shatabdi Nagar. As many as 4663 people had applied for these houses.

news.title: To escape law, Goa tweaks town & country planning act for land conversions
news.para: The Goa cabinet has replaced Section 16B of the Town and Country Planning Act with Section 39A. The new section allows the chief town planner to alter the Regional Plan or Outline Development Plan for land conversions.

news.title: Grasim Industries to start paints manufacturing in Dhanansu village of Ludhiana
news.para: The industry has completed the construction of its integrated paint-manufacturing unit at Hi-Tech Valley in Dhanansu village of Ludhiana.

news.title: Ahmedabad development body's plots sale in Bopal draws poor response
news.para: ​Despite hopes of raking in big bucks, Auda managed to secure bids for only two plots, and even these bids exceeded the base price by Rs 100 and Rs 200 per sq m.

news.title: DTCP ramps up checks, demolishes 12 houses in colony off Golf Course Road
news.para: The team comprising assistant town planner, junior engineer and field staff identified 12 under-construction houses that didn’t have a building plan and mandatory approvals.
